The paper deals with a graph problem, specifically the dispersion problem, which involves selecting nodes in a graph to maximize the minimum distance between any two chosen nodes. This problem is related to independent set and has applications in various fields such as wireless sensor networks and facility location. The paper focuses on the dispersion problem on trees and presents optimal and improved algorithms for both the unweighted and weighted cases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
